# Reverse proxy Nginx routing

- **Server name**: `web.xviewplusn2.com.mx`; listen `80`. Preserve `Host` and set `X-Forwarded-*` including `X-Forwarded-Proto` via the `map` + `$meg_x_forwarded_proto` pattern already in `nginx.conf`.
- **SQUID paths** (proxy to pool on `:3128`): `/RTEFacade`, `/compass`, `/search`, `/personalization`, `/SessionManagement` — use both exact (`location =`) and prefix (`location ^~ .../`) blocks where the repo already does.
- **BFF paths** (proxy to pools on `:80`): `/rtvbff/linear`, `/rtvbff/vod`, `/rtvbff/image` — `proxy_pass` must keep full URI semantics consistent with existing `location ^~` blocks.
- **Default**: `location /` should **fail closed** (`return 404`) for unknown paths unless product explicitly requires otherwise.
- **Upstream tuning**: keep `max_fails`, `fail_timeout`, and `keepalive` consistent with existing style when adding servers.
- When adding a route, follow `reverse-proxy/docs/04-como-agregar-rutas.md` and mirror changes in **both** `reverse-proxy/nginx/` and `roles/.../files/nginx/` trees.
